<h1 id=''>/</h1><h2 id='strong-em-get-em-strong'><strong><em>GET</em></strong></h2>
<p><strong>Summary:</strong> Get a bundle of appointments</p>

<p><strong>Description:</strong> RESTful searching for appointments by appointment start date is supported. See https://www.hl7.org/fhir/search.html for instructions on formatting search criteria. The following search prefixes are supported: lt, gt, eq, le, ge.</p>
<h3 id='http-request'>HTTP Request</h3>
<p><code>***GET*** /</code> </p>

<p><strong>Parameters</strong></p>

<table><thead>
<tr>
<th>Name</th>
<th>Located in</th>
<th>Description</th>
<th>Required</th>
<th>Type</th>
</tr>
</thead><tbody>
<tr>
<td>identifier</td>
<td>query</td>
<td>The unique identifier acquired from the appointment search</td>
<td>No</td>
<td>array</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>patient</td>
<td>query</td>
<td>The unique identifier acquired from the patient search</td>
<td>No</td>
<td>array</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>date</td>
<td>query</td>
<td>The collection of appointment date filters</td>
<td>No</td>
<td>array</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>nx-practice-id</td>
<td>header</td>
<td>The unique identifier for a practice</td>
<td>Yes</td>
<td>string</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>

<p><strong>Responses</strong></p>

<table><thead>
<tr>
<th>Code</th>
<th>Description</th>
</tr>
</thead><tbody>
<tr>
<td>200</td>
<td>Returns a bundle of appointments</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>400</td>
<td>No supported search parameters provided</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>404</td>
<td>Specified patient or patient appointments do not exist</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>500</td>
<td>Internal server error</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
